Problem Statement
Create an FAQ section where each question can be clicked to show or hide its answer. 
Both the question and its answer should be displayed as paragraphs, with the answer hidden by default.

Note: Use Inspect Element in your browser to understand how your code is operating.

Your Task
Create an HTML page that contains:
A <div> container with id faqSection to hold all FAQs.
Inside the container, create at least three question-and-answer pairs, each consisting of:
A <p> element for the question.
A <p> element for the answer, placed immediately after the question.
Keep all answer <p> elements hidden by default.
Write JavaScript code that performs the following:
When a user clicks on a question, show or hide the corresponding answer paragraph below it. 
(Hint: You may use nextElementSibling.)

